LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF IDAHO
Sixty-eighth Legislature First Regular Session - 2025
IN THE SENATE
SENATE BILL NO. 1111
BY STATE AFFAIRS COMMITTEE
1 AN ACT
2 RELATING TO THE CONSUMER PROTECTION ACT; AMENDING CHAPTER 6, TITLE 48, IDAHO
3 CODE, BY THE ADDITION OF A NEW SECTION 48-603H, IDAHO CODE, TO ESTABLISH
4 PROVISIONS REGARDING TRUTH IN DIGITAL ADVERTISING SALES; AND DECLARING
5 AN EMERGENCY AND PROVIDING AN EFFECTIVE DATE.
6 Be It Enacted by the Legislature of the State of Idaho:
7 SECTION 1. That Chapter 6, Title 48, Idaho Code, be, and the same is
8 hereby amended by the addition thereto of a NEW SECTION, to be known and des-
9 ignated as Section 48-603H, Idaho Code, and to read as follows:
10 48-603H. TRUTH IN DIGITAL ADVERTISING SALES. (1) For purposes of this
11 section:
12 (a) "Ad reach" means the number of unique individuals who see a digital
13 advertisement.
14 (b) "Click" means the interaction between a web user and an advertise-
15 ment on a website that occurs when a user selects an advertisement in
16 order to be taken to a different web page or different portion of a web
17 page.
18 (c) "Click-through rate" means the ratio of clicks to impressions.
19 (d) "Digital advertisement" means an advertisement on the internet,
20 including but not limited to websites, mobile phone applications, and
21 social media.
22 (e) "Digital advertiser" means a person who sells digital advertise-
23 ments.
24 (f) "Engagement rate" means the percentage of people who interact with
25 a digital advertisement.
26 (g) "Geo-targeted" or "geo-targeting" means a digital advertisement
27 that is specifically shown to and viewable by users located within a
28 designated geographic region, including but not limited to a state,
29 county, or zip code, allowing an ad to reach people only in such geo-
30 graphical area.
31 (h) "Impression" means a count of every time an advertisement, post, or
32 web page is displayed to a user.
33 (i) "Key performance indicator" means measurable indicators of a digi-
34 tal advertisement's success, including click-through rate, engagement
35 rate, length of impressions, and number of impressions.
36 (2) Within thirty (30) days after the term of a digital advertisement
37 expires, the purchaser of such digital advertisement may request verifica-
38 tion of any representation relating to key performance indicators or geo-
39 targeting made by the digital advertiser to the purchaser.
40 (3) Within thirty (30) days after the receipt of a request for veri-
41 fication pursuant to subsection (2) of this section, a digital advertiser
42 shall reply to the purchaser with key performance indicator verification

2
1 information, including the date, time, length of impression, and whether a
2 click-through occurred, if applicable. In addition, if a digital advertiser
3 represented that a digital advertisement would be geo-targeted, such adver-
4 tiser shall identify the geographical locations where clicks, engagements,
5 or impressions relating to the digital advertisement occurred with suffi-
6 cient specificity to demonstrate that the geo-targeting occurred.
7 (4) A digital advertiser who is not able to verify the key performance
8 indicators or geo-targeting information provided for in subsection (3) of
9 this section after having made representations that such indicators or geo-
10 targeting would be fulfilled commits a violation of this chapter. Pursuant
11 to section 48-608, Idaho Code, a purchaser of a digital advertisement from a
12 digital advertiser who violates the provisions of this section may bring an
13 action to recover actual damages. Alternatively, the purchaser, in lieu of
14 actual damages, may elect to recover a refund of fees paid for a digital ad-
15 vertisement and the sum of one thousand dollars ($1,000) per violation.
16 (5) A digital advertiser who does business in Idaho shall make avail-
17 able and shall maintain a method for a purchaser of a digital advertisement
18 to request verification pursuant to subsection (2) of this section and for
19 such purchaser to receive verification information from a digital adver-
20 tiser pursuant to the provisions of subsection (3) of this section.
21 SECTION 2. An emergency existing therefor, which emergency is hereby
22 declared to exist, this act shall be in full force and effect on and after
23 July 1, 2025.

